review_blob: Bomber from Capones. Pours an oily pitch black with a medium sized brown head. Aroma of bakers chocolate, dark chocolate, dark malt and cocoa. Taste is much the same as the aroma. Very dark chocolaty.
Bomber from Capones. Pours a pitch black with a large foamy beige/tan head. Aroma of chocolate peanut butter and roasted malt. Taste of chocolate, peanut butter and malt. Much like a dessert.
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Tower Tuesday: Infusion A - Coffee Porter

review_blob: 750 ml bottle purchased from the Canton location. Pours a cloudy unfiltered gold with a large white head. Aroma of freshly squeezed grapefruit, bitter hops, mango and pine. Taste of juicy grapefruit, bitter hops, mango, melon and peach. Another gem from Trillium.
Growler from Fermentaria. Pours a murky yellow orange sun with a medium sized soapy white head. Aroma of grapefruit, orange and hops. Taste is much the same.
beer_name: Tired Hands Waiting For The Blood

review_blob: Growler from Cafe. Pours cola black with a medium sized light brown head. Aroma of mild roasted malts, vanilla, graham crackers and blueberry. Taste is much the same as the aroma.

Bomber courtesy of Todd. Bottled 1/7/2015. Pours a dark maple brown cola with a medium sized beige head. Aroma of malt, chocolate and toffee. Taste of mild dark malt, toffee, chocolate and light caramel. Very mild.
Bomber courtesy of Todd. Bottled 12/29/15. Pours a deep copper amber with a medium sized off white head. Aroma of tangy citrus, toasty malt, grapefruit and hops. Taste is much the same as the aroma.
750 ml bottle Pours a cloudy gold with a medium sized white head. Aroma of saison yeast, oak and sour grapes. Taste is much the same as the aroma.

Growler from Fermentaria. Pours a reddish purple orange with a medium sized white head. Aroma of fruit punch, hibiscus flowers, rose juice and hops. Taste of fruit punch, rose juice, hops and hints of lemon.
2014 bomber. Pours a deep cloudy caramel amber with a medium sized cream colored head. Aroma of light whiskey, oak, vanilla and toffee. Taste is much the same as the aroma. Very mild for 11%.

Growler from Cafe. Pours a dark cola with a medium sized creamy tan head. Aroma of lightly roasted malt, plums, tobacco and cocoa. Taste of creamy roasted malt, plums, cocoa, light smoke and hints of tobacco.

Growler from TH. Pours a cranberry juice like deep red purple with a medium sized light pink/white head. Aroma of hibiscus, cinnamon sticks, vanilla, rice pudding, sour cherries and unripe berries. Taste of hibiscus, sour unsweet cherries, cinnamon and light cranberry. Nice blend.
Bomber courtesy of Todd. Pours a black cola with a medium sized tan/light brown head. Aroma of coffee and cream, oatmeal, roasted malt and chocolate. Taste is much the same. Excellent.

Bomber. Pours a dark caramel amber with a large fluffy cream colored head. Unfiltered, with lots of particles and sediment floating around. Aroma of hops, malt, toffee, orange citrus and light perfume. Taste of toffee, hops, orange citrus and grapefruit.

Growler from Fermentaria. Pours a semi clear light gold with a large crystalized white foamy head. Aroma of fresh hops,honeysuckle, grapefruit and grassy notes. Taste of fresh hops, watery grapefruit and honeysuckle. Aroma is amazing as it warms up.

12 oz bottle. Pours a pitch black with a medium sized tan/light brown head. Aroma of rich chocolate, fudge, roasted malt, black licorice, molasses and cayenne pepper. Taste of sweet chocolate, molasses, roasted malt, anise and cayenne pepper. Has a peppery finish.
beer_name: Bells Planet Series: Neptune - The Mystic

review_blob: 12 oz bottle. Pours a deep semi clear coppery amber with a medium sized cream colored head. Aroma of bourbon, oak, toffee, vanilla and candied sugar. Taste of candied sugar, bourbon, oak, vanilla and toffee.
beer_name: Bells Planet Series: Saturn - The Bringer Of Old Age

review_blob: 12 oz bottle, 2014 release. Pours pitch black with a medium sized light brown head. Aroma of coffee, milk chocolate , nuts and roasted malts. Taste is much the same as the aroma. Cant believe how light this is. Nice stuff.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: 12.7 oz bottle. Pours an oily pitch black with a medium brown head. Aroma of bourbon, dark malt, soy sauce, cacao nib, rich chocolate and coffee. Taste is much the same as the aroma.
beer_name: Lost Abbey Box Set: Track #10 (Bat out of Hell)

review_blob: 12 oz bottle. Pours pitch black with a medium sized brown head. Aroma of dark chocolate, milk chocolate, cocoa and roasted malt and pine. Taste of pine, dark chocolate, milk chocolate, cocoa, roasted malt and a hint of citrus. Excellent.
11.2 oz bottle courtesy of Sloth. Pours black/very dark brown with a small tan/light brown head. Aroma of coffee beans, dark chocolate and roasted malt. Taste is much the same.
beer_name: Brewfist / Prairie Artisan Ales Spaghetti Western

review_blob: Bomber courtesy of Todd. Pours a clear deep gold with a medium sized sudsy off white head. Aroma of crisp pilsener malts, grass and faint citrus. Taste is much the same as the aroma.
Growler from Cafe. Pours a hazy gold with a medium sized white head. Aroma of sweet lemon, melon, rye and hops. Taste is much the same.
Bottle purchased from HF in March 2014. Pours pitch black oil with a small brown head. Aroma of maple syrup, sweet bourbon, dark chocolate and dark malt. Taste is much the same. Sweet, yet mild.
beer_name: Hill Farmstead Beyond Good and Evil

review_blob: 12 oz bottle. Pours a clear deep gold with a medium sized frosty off white head. Aroma of light tropical fruit notes(mango, guava, pineapple) mild grapefruit and hops. Taste of hops, light melon, grapefruit and guava. Good session beer.
beer_name: Firestone Walker Luponic Distortion Revolution No. 001

review_blob: 750 ml bottle batch #3 purchased from Hill Farmstead. Pours a deep cloudy yellow gold with a large frosty white head. Aroma of Brett yeast, oak wood, and sour funk. Taste is much the same as the aroma.
12 oz bottle. Pours a clear liquid gold with a medium sized white head. Aroma of grapefruit, hops and agave syrup. Taste is much the same as the aroma.

Bomber. Pours a deep dark amber with a medium sized cream colored head. Aroma of grapefruit, rye, cola, wheat, toffee, grains and hops. Taste of Cascade and Centennial hops, grapefruit, rye, wheat, toffee and buckwheat.
Growler from Cafe. Pours a murky, muddy yellow gold with a medium sized frosty white head. Aroma of hops, guava, melon, peach and light coconut. Taste is much the same as the aroma. Juicy stuff.

Bomber. Bottled 2/4/2016. Pours a deep clear copper amber with a medium sized beige colored head. Aroma of toffee, dry fruit, orange, tangy lemon and hops. Taste of toffee, orange, light lemon, hops and dry fruit.

12 oz can. Pours a clear gold with a large foamy white head. Aroma of pilsner malts, faint hops and light floral notes. Taste of pilsner malts, light hops and faint floral notes. Similar to Prima Pils.
Growler from Fermentaria. Pours a murky orange yellow gold with a large sudsy white head. Aroma of juicy hops, passion fruit, mango, guava and grapefruit. Taste is much the same as the aroma.

Pint can courtesy of Todd. Pours a deep cloudy dark rusty orange with a medium sized cream colored head. Aroma of malted rye, tea leaves, hops and floral notes. Taste of rye malt, hops and tea leaves.
Growler from Fermentaria. Pours a murky gray yellow with a medium sized off white head. Aroma of melon, cantaloupe, pineapple, peach and hops. Taste of hops, pineapple, peach and melon.
12 oz bottle. Pours a black cola with a medium sized light brown head. Aroma of roasted malt, coffee beans, hops and light citrus. Taste of roasted malt, coffee beans and dark chocolate.
Growler from one of the locations. Pours a cloudy, murky gold with a medium sized fluffy white head. Aroma of hops, melon, lemon, grapefruit and funk. Taste of melon, lemon, hops and grapefruit.

Draft at Fermentaria. Pours a cloudy yellow straw gold with a medium sized white head. Aroma of mosaic hops, oats, spelt, lemon and tropical fruit notes. Taste is much the same as the aroma. Crisp and refreshing.
Draft at Cafe. Pours a mahogany amber color with a small beige head. Aroma of licorice root, light cinnamon and malt. Taste is much the same as the aroma.
Draft at Fermentaria. Pours a cloudy yellow gold with a frosty medium sized white head. Aroma of oak, saison yeast and lemon. Taste is much the same. RIP LEMMY KILMISTER.
12 oz bottle. Pours a clear deep gold with a frosty medium sized white head. Aroma of pineapple, mango and hops. Taste of pineapple, mango, sweet grapefruit and hops.

32 oz growler from Cafe. Pours a murky orange gold with a medium white head. Aroma of apples, cayenne pepper, light funk, saison yeast and lemon. Taste of saison yeast, light funk, lemon, apples and cayenne pepper.

# 2500 2006 750 ml bottle. #62/235. Pours a pitch black oily color with a tiny brown top. Aroma of dark chocolate, bourbon, vanilla, oak, coffee beans, barley, prunes, plums and soy sauce. Taste of dark chocolate, bourbon, vanilla, oak, coffee beans, roasted dark malt, barley, prunes and soy sauce.
beer_name: AleSmith Speedway Stout - Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: Pint can at Blackback Pub 9/23/2015. Pours a cloudy deep yellow gold with a medium sized frosty white head. Aroma of bitter hops, grassy notes, spruce and earth. Taste of spruce, bitter hops, earth and grassy notes.
12 oz bottle. Pours a clear deep gold with a frosty medium sized off white head. Aroma of cantaloupe, mango, melon, citrus and faint pine. Taste is much the same as the aroma. Crisp and refreshing.

12 oz can purchased from brewery. Stamped 9/16/2015. Pours a cloudy light yellow gold with a large foamy white head. Aroma of pine, spruce, lemon, grapefruit and hops. Taste of spruce, pine, lemon, hops and grapefruit. Excellent session beer. Fiddlehead, PLEASE MAKE MORE of this !!

750 ml bottle. Pours black with a medium sized beige/light tan head. Aroma of slightly burnt toast, toffee, light chocolate, malt and hints of black licorice. Taste of toffee, milk chocolate, malt and bread.
Growler from Fermentaria. Pours a dark cola color with a medium sized foamy tan head. Aroma of pine tar, oats, black wheat, hops and grapefruit. Taste is much the same as the aroma.
12 oz can. Pours a cloudy deep yellow gold with a frosty medium sized white head. Aroma of pilsner malt, lemon, Galaxy hops and grapefruit. Taste is much the same. Good stuff.
beer_name: Long Trail Smash Project #1 - Pilsner Malt / Galaxy Hops

review_blob: 2015 vintage. 12 oz bottle courtesy of Todd. Pours a black cola with a medium sized tan head. Aroma of bourbon, toasted malts, vanilla, dark fruit and sugar cookies. Taste of smooth bourbon, dark malt, vanilla, and dark fruit. Excellent.
beer_name: Central Waters Brewers Reserve Bourbon Barrel Scotch Ale

review_blob: ist rating. Growler from the source. Pours a hazy orange golden yellow straw with a medium sized white head. Aroma is peppery with notes of bubble gum, citrus, lemon and saison yeast. Taste of saison yeast, peppery notes, lemon, orange, grapefruit and hops. Very nice.
